commit.message: Add table of contents to the API docs.
Add default ports for various schemes.
Export metadata variables properly (furl.__title__, furl.__version__, etc).
Update orderedmultidict to v1.0.1 to resolve 'DeprecationWarning: Using or importing the ABCs from 'collections' instead of from 'collections.abc' is deprecated, and in 3.8 it will stop working'.
Add an __idiv()__ path manipulation example to the README.
Append slash to paths to intimate a directory, test -> test/.
Add trailing comma for consistent code style.
Add more tests and a changelog entry for the new query_dont_quote= and dont_quote= parameters.
Expound upon the comment of the dont_quote= parameter of Query.encode().
Support unicode usernames and passwords in Python 2.
Use string formatting over the more opaque str.join().
Move package info from __init__.py into the more standard __version__.py.
Always encode '&' is queries, even with quote_dont_quote=True. This, in turn, allows URLs as query parameters.
